        "## QUESTION 1\n",
        "\n",
        "__Write an SQL query that provides playerID, yearID, and batting average for players with at least 1 at bat that year. Sort the table from highest batting average to lowest, and then by playerid alphabetically. Show the top 5 results in your report.__\n",
        "\n",
        "Here we can create a new column, using the already established columns for hits and at bats to calculate and save the batting average. But we're not filtering out the players that had few at bats, we take all players who got up to the plate at least once and evaluate them, showing in our results high batting averages because of few at bats. "
      ],
      "id": "c56bb47a"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Include and execute your code here\n",
        "\n",
        "# The code below can serve as a template for all the rest of your queries. It is just missing the\n",
        "# SQL code. Put your SQL query in between the triple quotation marks to create the query. The records will be stored in 'results', which is a polars data frame\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        "    SELECT playerID, yearID,H,  AB, CAST (H AS FLOAT) / AB AS batting\n",
        "    FROM batting\n",
        "    WHERE AB >= 1\n",
        "    ORDER BY batting DESC, playerID\n",
        "    LIMIT 5;\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "results = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "results\n"
      ],
      "id": "d828d21e",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
