      "source": [
        "## QUESTION 3\n",
        "\n",
        "__Now modify the SQL query to calculate the batting average for players over their entire careers (all years combined). Only include players with at least 100 at bats over their entire career, and print the top 5 results.__\n",
        "\n",
        "Here we use the same logic, but group our players together by playerID and sum their hits and at bats. Now we can see their career stats, and the five highest career players.  "
      ],
      "id": "1529829d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Include and execute your code here\n",
        "q = \"\"\"\n",
        "    SELECT playerID,  \n",
        "    SUM(H) AS total_hits,\n",
        "    SUM(AB) AS total_at_bat, \n",
        "    CAST (SUM(H) AS FLOAT) / SUM(AB) AS batting\n",
        "    FROM batting\n",
        "    GROUP BY playerID, yearID\n",
        "    HAVING SUM(AB) >= 100\n",
        "    ORDER BY batting DESC, playerID\n",
        "    LIMIT 5;\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "results = pl.read_database(q, con)\n",
        "results"
      ],
